(42, 24, 52, 43, 16, 22, 22, 'great joy', 'Joy in Worship and Reunion', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy following a significant encounter with Jesus. In Luke, the disciples return with ''great joy'' after worshipping Him, while in John, Jesus promises that their sorrow will turn to joy when they see Him again.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 24, 52, 43, 20, 28, 28, 'worshipped him', 'Worship and Divine Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of worship and recognition of Jesus'' divine nature. In both passages, the act of worship is emphasized, with the disciples worshipping Him in Luke and Thomas declaring Him as ''My Lord and my God'' in John.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 24, 52, 60, 1, 8, 8, 'great joy', 'Joy in Belief and Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy associated with faith and worship. In Luke, the disciples return with ''great joy'' after worshipping, while in 1 Peter, believers rejoice with ''joy unspeakable'' despite not seeing Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
